dw.com
Database: Tropes in Oscar-eligible movies
21.02.2019

Ahead of the Oscars, DW wanted to look at what film chlichés say about Hollywood. So we analyzed the TVTropes.org entries for 6637 Oscar-eligible movies from 1929 to 2019. On this page, you have the opportunity to search the data that was the basis for this analysis.

Read the stories that came out of this analysis:

1. The Oscar Academy's taste in movies

How does the Academy pick an Oscar nominee? Our data analysis shows which tropes help a movie get nominated as "Best Picture". Hint: Drama helps. So does alcohol.

by Laura Döing and Kira Schacht
English | German

2. What Hollywood movies do to perpetuate racial stereotypes

Movies reflect stereotypes, but they also shape them. If Asians are portrayed as nerdy, black men as dangerous and Latinas as fiery, it influences perceptions. So what exactly does Hollywood have to say about various ethnic groups?

by Kira Schacht
English | German

This table contains a list of tropes found in the 6637 Oscar-eligible movies we analyzed. The full list contains 21789 tropes and can be found in our GitHub repository (see link below). To improve loading time, this table is filtered to only include tropes that have been found in at least 10 movies.

For further information on our sources, as well as the data cleaning and analysis process, please refer to this github repository for reference.

In case you have questions or find errors, feel free to get in touch: design.data[at]dw[dot]com
